{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e9162478-32d7-4705-bd06-4174777c7169","content":"Here's what I found in `my_app/views.py`:\n\n**Line 3: `datetime.now()`** — Hard-coded static call inside the function body. This is untestable because you can't easily mock or freeze time in tests.\n\n### Recommended fix\n\nInject the clock dependency so tests can substitute it:\n\n```python\nfrom django.utils import timezone\n\ndef index(request, now=None):\n    now = now or timezone.now()\n    return render(request, 'index.html', {'time': now})\n```\n\nOr use `django.utils.timezone.now()` with [`freezegun`](https://github.com/spulec/freezegun) in tests:\n\n```python\nfrom freezegun import freeze_time\n\n@freeze_time(\"2026-04-28\")\ndef test_index(self):\n    response = self.client.get(\"/\")\n    ...\n```\n\n**Summary:** Only 1 file with 1 untestable static (`datetime.now()` on line 3). Also note it's using `datetime.now()` instead of Django's timezone-aware `timezone.now()`, which will produce naive datetimes if `USE_TZ = True`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"605f4289-e1d8-4310-b212-01f3fb30d447","outputTokens":277,"requestId":"0C09:3131A1:67E6D75:7132D7A:69F01FEB"},"id":"ba4ebe68-8632-405e-ab90-1e1eadb96390","timestamp":"2026-04-28T02:48:18.297Z","parentId":"3e17c28c-d963-496e-a47c-4089c863a255"}
